c benefits of education and critically assesses the validity and usefulness of the idea of systemic or standards-based reform. Finally he develops a conceptual framework for mapping and analyzing education research and reform activities.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aEducation and statezUnited States. 0aEducationxResearchzUnited States. 0aEducationzUnited StatesxHistory. 0aFederal aid to educationzUnited States. 7aEDUCATION / Educational Policy & Reform / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z97831105379940 cprintz978030007571740uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030014722340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300147223423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300147223/original  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY